<section id="htmlvorlagen">
<paragraph role="heading" id="hd_id3156014" xml-lang="en-US" level="1" l10n="CHG" oldref="1"><link href="text/shared/07/09000000.xhp" name="Web Pages">Web Pages</link></paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3146946" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="2">To create a new web page for the Internet, open a new <emph>HTML Document</emph> by choosing <emph>File - New</emph>.</paragraph>
</section>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3143284" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="CHG" oldref="3">A tool for creating new web pages is the Web Layout mode, which you enable with <emph>View - Web Layout</emph>.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="heading" id="hd_id3147285" xml-lang="en-US" level="2" l10n="U" oldref="8">Creating a New Web Page</paragraph>
<list type="unordered">
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3150808" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="CHG" oldref="9">Switch to the web layout mode by choosing <emph>View - Web Layout</emph> or by opening a new HTML document.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3145136" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="CHG" oldref="15">To create an HTML page from your $[officename] document, save the page using one of the "HTML Document" file types.</paragraph>
</listitem>
